title: Independent candidate Mujahid Ali wins NA-21 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate, Mujahid Ali has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-21, Mardan-I by securing 116,049 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan candidate, Azam Khan who bagged 60,373 votes.
The votersâ€™ turn-out remained 46.90%.
